ity of the classical result is discussed. The result is analyzed\nfrom the viewpoint of the deWitt - Brehme - Hobbs equation (and corresponding\nequations in higher dimensions).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Oct 2013 21:43:56 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-01-24"}
