and surface of the disk, $ \\theta_{0} < \\theta < \\theta_{s} $. In this area,\nthe accretion flow moves away from the central object. The third region, which\nis located between the surface of the disk and the polar axis, is called wind\nregion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Oct 2013 16:41:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-17"}
